934                         next_state_proc : process(
935                             curr_state, err_frm_req, ctrl_ctr_zero, no_data_field, is_receiver, is_fd_frame,
936                             is_bus_off, go_to_suspend, tx_frame_ready, mr_command_ercrst_q, reinteg_ctr_expired,

938                             mr_mode_rom)
939                         begin
940        1/1                  next_state <= curr_state;
941                     
942        1/1                  if (err_frm_req = '1') then
943        1/1                      if (mr_mode_rom = ROM_DISABLED) then
944        1/1                          if (is_err_active = '1') then
945        1/1                              next_state <= s_pc_act_err_flag;
946                                     else
947        1/1                              next_state <= s_pc_pas_err_flag;
948                                     end if;
949                                 else
950        1/1                          next_state <= s_pc_integrating;
951                                 end if;
952                     
953                             else
954        1/1                      case curr_state is
955                     
956                                 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
957                                 -- Unit is Off
958                                 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
959                                 when s_pc_off =>
960        1/1                          next_state <= s_pc_integrating;
961                     
962                                 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
963                                 -- Unit is integrating (first integration after enabling)
964                                 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
965                                 when s_pc_integrating =>
966        1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
967        1/1                              next_state <= s_pc_idle;
968                                     end if;
969                     
970                                 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
971                                 -- Start of frame
972                                 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
973                                 when s_pc_sof =>
974        1/1                          next_state <= s_pc_base_id;
975                     
976                                 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
977                                 -- Base identifier
978                                 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
979                                 when s_pc_base_id =>
980        1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
981        1/1                              next_state <= s_pc_rtr_srr_r1;
982                                     end if;
983                     
984                                 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
985                                 -- RTR/SRR/R1 bit. First bit after Base identifier.
986                                 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
987                                 when s_pc_rtr_srr_r1 =>
988        1/1                          next_state <= s_pc_ide;
989                     
990                                 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
991                                 -- IDE bit
992                                 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
993                                 when s_pc_ide =>
994        1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
995        1/1                             next_state <= s_pc_edl_r0;
996                                     else
997        1/1                             next_state <= s_pc_ext_id;
998                                     end if;
999                     
1000                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1001                                -- Extended identifier
1002                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1003                                when s_pc_ext_id =>
1004       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
1005       1/1                              next_state <= s_pc_rtr_r1;
1006                                    end if;
1007                    
1008                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1009                                -- RTR/R1 bit after the Extended identifier
1010                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1011                                when s_pc_rtr_r1 =>
1012       1/1                          next_state <= s_pc_edl_r1;
1013                    
1014                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1015                                -- EDL/r1 bit after RTR/r1 bit in Extended Identifier
1016                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1017                                when s_pc_edl_r1 =>
1018       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
1019       1/1                              next_state <= s_pc_r0_ext;
1020                                    else
1021       1/1                              if (pex_on_fdf_enable = '1') then
1022       1/1                                  next_state <= s_pc_integrating;
1023                                        else
1024       1/1                                  next_state <= s_pc_r0_fd;
1025                                        end if;
1026                                    end if;
1027                    
1028                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1029                                -- r0 bit after EDL/r1 bit in Extended CAN Frames.
1030                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1031                                when s_pc_r0_ext =>
1032       1/1                          next_state <= s_pc_dlc;
1033                    
1034                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1035                                -- r0(res) bit in CAN FD Frames (both Base and Extended identifier)
1036                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1037                                when s_pc_r0_fd =>
1038       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE and pex_on_res_enable = '1') then
1039       1/1                              next_state <= s_pc_integrating;
1040                                    else
1041       1/1                              next_state <= s_pc_brs;
1042                                    end if;
1043                    
1044                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1045                                -- EDL/r0 bit in CAN 2.0 and CAN FD Frames with BASE identifier only!
1046                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1047                                when s_pc_edl_r0 =>
1048       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
1049       1/1                              next_state <= s_pc_dlc;
1050                                    else
1051                                        -- Protocol exception on recessive FDF/EDL in "Classical CAN" configuration
1052       1/1                              if (pex_on_fdf_enable = '1') then
1053       1/1                                  next_state <= s_pc_integrating;
1054                                        else
1055       1/1                                  next_state <= s_pc_r0_fd;
1056                                        end if;
1057                                    end if;
1058                    
1059                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1060                                -- BRS (Bit rate shift) Bit
1061                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1062                                when s_pc_brs =>
1063       1/1                          next_state <= s_pc_esi;
1064                    
1065                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1066                                -- ESI (Error State Indicator) Bit
1067                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1068                                when s_pc_esi =>
1069       1/1                          next_state <= s_pc_dlc;
1070                    
1071                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1072                                -- DLC (Data length code)
1073                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1074                                when s_pc_dlc =>
1075       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
1076       1/1                              if (no_data_field = '1') then
1077       1/1                                  if (go_to_stuff_count = '1') then
1078       1/1                                      next_state <= s_pc_stuff_count;
1079                                            else
1080       1/1                                      next_state <= s_pc_crc;
1081                                            end if;
1082                                        else
1083       1/1                                  next_state <= s_pc_data;
1084                                        end if;
1085                                    end if;
1086                    
1087                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1088                                -- Data field
1089                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1090                                when s_pc_data =>
1091       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
1092       1/1                              if (go_to_stuff_count = '1') then
1093       1/1                                  next_state <= s_pc_stuff_count;
1094                                        else
1095       1/1                                  next_state <= s_pc_crc;
1096                                        end if;
1097                                    end if;
1098                    
1099                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1100                                -- Stuff count + Stuff parity field
1101                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1102                                when s_pc_stuff_count =>
1103       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
1104       1/1                              next_state <= s_pc_crc;
1105                                    end if;
1106                    
1107                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1108                                -- CRC field
1109                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1110                                when s_pc_crc =>
1111       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
1112       1/1                              next_state <= s_pc_crc_delim;
1113                                    end if;
1114                    
1115                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1116                                -- CRC Delimiter
1117                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1118                                when s_pc_crc_delim =>
1119       1/1                          if (is_fd_frame = '1') then
1120       1/1                              next_state <= s_pc_ack_fd_1;
1121                                    else
1122       1/1                              next_state <= s_pc_ack;
1123                                    end if;
1124                    
1125                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1126                                -- ACK Slot of CAN 2.0 frame
1127                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1128                                when s_pc_ack =>
1129       1/1                          next_state <= s_pc_ack_delim;
1130                    
1131                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1132                                -- First bit of CAN FD Frame ACK
1133                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1134                                when s_pc_ack_fd_1 =>
1135       1/1                          next_state <= s_pc_ack_fd_2;
1136                    
1137                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1138                                -- Second bit of CAN FD Frame ACK
1139                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1140                                when s_pc_ack_fd_2 =>
1141       1/1                          next_state <= s_pc_ack_delim;
1142                    
1143                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1144                                -- ACK Delimiter
1145                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1146                                when s_pc_ack_delim =>
1147       1/1                          next_state <= s_pc_eof;
1148                    
1149                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1150                                -- End of Frame. Receiver sampling DOMINANT in last bit interprets this as
1151                                -- Overload flag.
1152                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1153                                when s_pc_eof =>
1154       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
1155       1/1                              if (rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE) then
1156       1/1                                  next_state <= s_pc_intermission;
1157                                        elsif (is_receiver = '1') then
1158       1/1                                  if (mr_mode_rom = ROM_DISABLED) then
1159       1/1                                      next_state <= s_pc_ovr_flag;
1160                                            else
1161       1/1                                      next_state <= s_pc_integrating;
1162                                            end if;
1163                                        end if;
1164                                    end if;
1165                    
1166                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1167                                -- Intermission field
1168                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1169                                when s_pc_intermission =>
1170       1/1                          if (is_bus_off = '1') then
1171       1/1                              next_state <= s_pc_reintegrating_wait;
1172                    
1173                                    -- Last bit of intermission!
1174                                    elsif (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
1175       1/1                              if (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
1176       1/1                                  next_state <= s_pc_base_id;
1177                                        elsif (go_to_suspend = '1') then
1178       1/1                                  next_state <= s_pc_suspend;
1179                                        elsif (tx_frame_ready = '1') then
1180       1/1                                  next_state <= s_pc_sof;
1181                                        else
1182       1/1                                  next_state <= s_pc_idle;
1183                                        end if;
1184                    
1185                                    -- First or second bit of intermission!
1186                                    elsif (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
1187       1/1                              if (mr_mode_rom = ROM_DISABLED) then
1188       1/1                                  next_state <= s_pc_ovr_flag;
1189                                        else
1190       1/1                                  next_state <= s_pc_integrating;
1191                                        end if;
1192                                    end if;
1193                    
1194                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1195                                -- Suspend transmission
1196                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1197                                when s_pc_suspend =>
1198       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
1199       1/1                              next_state <= s_pc_base_id;
1200                                    elsif (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
1201                                        -- Start transmission after suspend if we have what to
1202                                        -- transmitt!
1203       1/1                              if (tx_frame_ready = '1') then
1204       1/1                                  next_state <= s_pc_sof;
1205                                        else
1206       1/1                                  next_state <= s_pc_idle;
1207                                        end if;
1208                                    end if;
1209                    
1210                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1211                                -- Unit is in Bus idle period.
1212                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1213                                when s_pc_idle =>
1214       1/1                         if (is_bus_off = '1') then
1215       1/1                             next_state <= s_pc_reintegrating_wait;
1216                                   elsif (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
1217       1/1                             next_state <= s_pc_base_id;
1218                                   elsif (tx_frame_ready = '1') then
1219       1/1                             next_state <= s_pc_sof;
1220                                   end if;
1221                    
1222                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1223                                -- Wait till command from User to start re-integration!
1224                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1225                                when s_pc_reintegrating_wait =>
1226       1/1                          if (mr_command_ercrst_q = '1') then
1227       1/1                              next_state <= s_pc_reintegrating;
1228                                    end if;
1229                    
1230                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1231                                -- Unit is re-integrating, waiting till re-integration counter expires!
1232                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1233                                when s_pc_reintegrating =>
1234       1/1                          if (reinteg_ctr_expired = '1' and ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
1235       1/1                              next_state <= s_pc_idle;
1236                                    end if;
1237                    
1238                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1239                                -- Active error flag.
1240                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1241                                when s_pc_act_err_flag =>
1242       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
1243       1/1                              next_state <= s_pc_err_delim_wait;
1244                                    end if;
1245                    
1246                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1247                                -- Passive error flag.
1248                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1249                                when s_pc_pas_err_flag =>
1250       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
1251       1/1                              next_state <= s_pc_err_delim_wait;
1252                                    end if;
1253                    
1254                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1255                                -- Wait till Error delimiter (detection of recessive bit)
1256                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1257                                when s_pc_err_delim_wait =>
1258       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE) then
1259       1/1                              next_state <= s_pc_err_delim;
1260                                    elsif (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
1261       1/1                              next_state <= s_pc_err_flag_too_long;
1262                                    end if;
1263                    
1264                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1265                                -- 13 dominant bits (6 Error flag + 7 Error delimiter) has been detected.
1266                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1267                                when s_pc_err_flag_too_long =>
1268       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE) then
1269       1/1                              next_state <= s_pc_err_delim;
1270                                    end if;
1271                    
1272                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1273                                -- 13 dominant bits (6 Overload flag + 7 Overload delimiter) has been detected.
1274                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1275                                when s_pc_ovr_flag_too_long =>
1276       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE) then
1277       1/1                              next_state <= s_pc_ovr_delim;
1278                                    end if;
1279                    
1280                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1281                                -- Error delimiter
1282                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1283                                when s_pc_err_delim =>
1284       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
1285       1/1                              if (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
1286       1/1                                  next_state <= s_pc_ovr_flag;
1287                                        else
1288       1/1                                  next_state <= s_pc_intermission;
1289                                        end if;
1290                                    end if;
1291                    
1292                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1293                                -- Overload flag
1294                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1295                                when s_pc_ovr_flag =>
1296       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
1297       1/1                              next_state <= s_pc_ovr_delim_wait;
1298                                    end if;
1299                    
1300                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1301                                -- Wait till overload delimiter.
1302                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1303                                when s_pc_ovr_delim_wait =>
1304       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE) then
1305       1/1                              next_state <= s_pc_ovr_delim;
1306                                    elsif (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
1307       1/1                              next_state <= s_pc_ovr_flag_too_long;
1308                                    end if;
1309                    
1310                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1311                                -- Overload delimiter
1312                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1313                                when s_pc_ovr_delim  =>
1314       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
1315       1/1                              if (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
1316       1/1                                  next_state <= s_pc_ovr_flag;
1317                                        else
1318       1/1                                  next_state <= s_pc_intermission;
1319                                        end if;
1320                                    end if;
1321                                end case;
1322                            end if;
1323                        end process;

1417                            -- Transceiver delay measurement
1418       1/1                  ssp_reset_i             <= '0';
1419       1/1                  tran_delay_meas         <= '0';
1420                    
1421                            -- Secondary sampling point control
1422       1/1                  btmc_reset              <= '0';
1423       1/1                  dbt_measure_start       <= '0';
1424       1/1                  gen_first_ssp           <= '0';
1425                    
1426                            -- Fault confinement
1427       1/1                  primary_err_i           <= '0';
1428       1/1                  err_delim_late_i        <= '0';
1429       1/1                  first_err_delim_d       <= '0';
1430       1/1                  set_err_active_i        <= '0';
1431                    
1432       1/1                  br_shifted_i            <= '0';
1433                    
1434                            -- Bit Stuffing/Destuffing control
1435       1/1                  stuff_length            <= std_logic_vector(to_unsigned(5, 3));
1436       1/1                  fixed_stuff             <= '0';
1437       1/1                  stuff_enable_set        <= '0';
1438       1/1                  stuff_enable_clear      <= '0';
1439       1/1                  destuff_enable_set      <= '0';
1440       1/1                  destuff_enable_clear    <= '0';
1441       1/1                  tx_frame_no_sof_d       <= '0';
1442                    
1443                            -- Synchronisation control
1444       1/1                  perform_hsync           <= '0';
1445                    
1446                            -- TXT Buffer pointer
1447       1/1                  txtb_ptr_d              <= 0;
1448                    
1449                            -- CRC control
1450       1/1                  crc_enable              <= '0';
1451       1/1                  crc_spec_enable_i       <= '0';
1452       1/1                  load_init_vect_i        <= '0';
1453                    
1454                            -- Bit time counters enabling
1455       1/1                  nbt_ctrs_en             <= '1';
1456       1/1                  dbt_ctrs_en             <= '0';
1457                    
1458                            -- Clear block register for retransmitt counter add signal.
1459       1/1                  retr_ctr_add_block_clr  <= '0';
1460       1/1                  tick_state_reg          <= '0';
1461                    
1462                            -- Status signals for debug
1463       1/1                  pc_dbg.is_control       <= '0';
1464       1/1                  pc_dbg.is_data          <= '0';
1465       1/1                  pc_dbg.is_stuff_count   <= '0';
1466       1/1                  pc_dbg.is_crc           <= '0';
1467       1/1                  pc_dbg.is_crc_delim     <= '0';
1468       1/1                  pc_dbg.is_ack           <= '0';
1469       1/1                  pc_dbg.is_ack_delim     <= '0';
1470       1/1                  pc_dbg.is_eof           <= '0';
1471       1/1                  pc_dbg.is_suspend       <= '0';
1472       1/1                  pc_dbg.is_err           <= '0';
1473       1/1                  pc_dbg.is_overload      <= '0';
1474       1/1                  pc_dbg.is_intermission  <= '0';
1475       1/1                  pc_dbg.is_sof           <= '0';
1476                    
1477       1/1                  clr_bus_off_rst_flg     <= '0';
1478       1/1                  decrement_rec_i         <= '0';
1479       1/1                  ack_err_flag_clr        <= '0';
1480       1/1                  bit_err_after_ack_err   <= '0';
1481                    
1482       1/1                  pexs_set                <= '0';
1483                    
1484       1/1                  if (err_frm_req = '1') then
1485       1/1                      tick_state_reg <= '1';
1486       1/1                      ctrl_ctr_pload_i   <= '1';
1487       1/1                      if (mr_mode_rom = ROM_DISABLED) then
1488       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_ERR_FLG_DURATION;
1489                                else
1490       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_INTEGRATION_DURATION;
1491       1/1                          set_idle_i <= '1';
1492                                end if;
1493       1/1                      rec_abort_d <= '1';
1494                    
1495       1/1                      crc_clear_match_flag <= '1';
1496       1/1                      destuff_enable_clear <= '1';
1497       1/1                      stuff_enable_clear <= '1';
1498                    
1499       1/1                      if (sp_control_q_i = DATA_SAMPLE or
1500                                    sp_control_q_i = SECONDARY_SAMPLE)
1501                                then
1502       1/1                          sp_control_switch_nominal <= '1';
1503       1/1                          br_shifted_i <= '1';
1504                                end if;
1505                    
1506       1/1                      if (is_transmitter = '1' and block_txtb_unlock = '0') then
1507       1/1                          txtb_hw_cmd_d.unlock <= '1';
1508       1/1                          if (tx_failed = '1') then
1509       1/1                              txtb_hw_cmd_d.failed  <= '1';
1510                                    else
1511       1/1                              txtb_hw_cmd_d.err     <= '1';
1512                                    end if;
1513                                end if;
1514                    
1515                                -- Keep both counters enabled to make sure that Error frame starts at proper time when
1516                                -- error occurred in Data Bit-rate.
1517       1/1                      dbt_ctrs_en <= '1';
1518                    
1519                            else
1520       1/1                      case curr_state is
1521                    
1522                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1523                                -- Unit is Off
1524                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1525                                when s_pc_off =>
1526       1/1                          if (mr_settings_ena = CTU_CAN_ENABLED) then
1527       1/1                              nbt_ctrs_en <= '1';
1528       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
1529       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
1530       1/1                              bit_err_disable <= '1';
1531                    
1532                                        -- If we receive recessive, then set reintegration counter only to 10 (already
1533                                        -- one bit was measured)! During this state, whole TSEG1 already elapsed!
1534       1/1                              if (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
1535       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_INTEGRATION_DURATION;
1536                                        else
1537       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_FIRST_INTEGRATION_DURATION;
1538                                        end if;
1539                                    end if;
1540                    
1541                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1542                                -- Unit is integrating (first integration after enabling)
1543                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1544                                when s_pc_integrating =>
1545       1/1                          bit_err_disable <= '1';
1546       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_ena <= '1';
1547       1/1                          perform_hsync <= '1';
1548                    
1549                                    -- Restart integration upon reception of DOMINANT bit or upon synchronization edge
1550                                    -- detected!
1551       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT or sync_edge = '1') then
1552       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_INTEGRATION_DURATION;
1553                                    end if;
1554                    
1555                                    -- When preloaded due to synchronisation edge, this is outside of sample point!
1556       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
1557       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
1558                                    end if;
1559                    
1560       1/1                          if (sync_edge = '1' and
1561                                       -- Third reset condition shall be valid for nodes which are CAN FD tolerant or
1562                                       -- CAN FD enabled!
1563                                       (not(mr_settings_pex = '0' and mr_mode_fde = '0')))
1564                                    then
1565       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_unaliged <= '1';
1566                                    end if;
1567                    
1568       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
1569       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
1570       1/1                              set_idle_i <= '1';
1571                    
1572                                        -- Device can be integrating right after start or after protocol exception.
1573                                        -- Only after start, it is bus off, then it shall be set to error active and
1574                                        -- error counters shall be cleared. Otherwise, error counters shall retain
1575                                        -- their value!
1576       1/1                              if (is_bus_off = '1') then
1577       1/1                                  set_err_active_i <= '1';
1578                                        end if;
1579       1/1                              load_init_vect_i <= '1';
1580                                    end if;
1581                    
1582                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1583                                -- Start of frame
1584                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1585                                when s_pc_sof =>
1586       1/1                          tick_state_reg <= '1';
1587       1/1                          bit_err_disable <= '1';
1588       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
1589       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_BASE_ID_DURATION;
1590       1/1                          tx_load_base_id_i <= '1';
1591       1/1                          sof_pulse_i <= '1';
1592       1/1                          tx_dominant <= '1';
1593       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_SOF;
1594       1/1                          crc_enable <= '1';
1595       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_sof <= '1';
1596                    
1597                                    -- If we have transmission pending, FSM goes to SOF in sample point of third bit of
1598                                    -- intermission or in idle. But till the end of bit, it is still Intermission/Idle
1599                                    -- from bus perspective, so we must allow hard-synchronization! Then, even during
1600                                    -- TSEG1 of SOF bit, we can keep hard-sync enabled, because it should be disabled
1601                                    -- due to no_pos_resync. since DUT sends dominant bit, and sync edge during TSEG1
1602                                    -- means positive phase error! Therefore any sync_edge will be ignored by prescaler!
1603       1/1                          perform_hsync <= '1';
1604                    
1605       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE) then
1606       1/1                              form_err_i <= '1';
1607                                    end if;
1608                    
1609                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1610                                -- Base identifier
1611                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1612                                when s_pc_base_id =>
1613       1/1                          bit_err_disable <= '1';
1614       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_ena <= '1';
1615       1/1                          rx_shift_ena <= "1111";
1616       1/1                          is_arbitration_i <= '1';
1617       1/1                          tx_shift_ena_i <= '1';
1618       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_ARB;
1619       1/1                          crc_enable <= '1';
1620       1/1                          arbitration_part <= ALC_BASE_ID;
1621                    
1622       1/1                          if (arbitration_lost_condition = '1') then
1623       1/1                              txtb_hw_cmd_d.unlock <= '1';
1624       1/1                              arbitration_lost_i <= '1';
1625       1/1                              stuff_enable_clear <= '1';
1626       1/1                              if (tx_failed = '1') then
1627       1/1                                  txtb_hw_cmd_d.failed  <= '1';
1628                                        else
1629       1/1                                  txtb_hw_cmd_d.arbl    <= '1';
1630                                        end if;
1631                                    end if;
1632                    
1633       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
1634       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
1635       1/1                              rx_store_base_id_i <= '1';
1636                                    end if;
1637                    
1638       1/1                          if (tx_data_wbs = DOMINANT and rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE) then
1639       1/1                              bit_err_arb_i <= '1';
1640                                    end if;
1641                    
1642                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1643                                -- RTR/SRR/R1 bit. First bit after Base identifier.
1644                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1645                                when s_pc_rtr_srr_r1 =>
1646       1/1                          tick_state_reg <= '1';
1647       1/1                          is_arbitration_i <= '1';
1648       1/1                          bit_err_disable <= '1';
1649       1/1                          crc_enable <= '1';
1650       1/1                          rx_store_rtr_i <= '1';
1651       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_ARB;
1652       1/1                          arbitration_part <= ALC_SRR_RTR;
1653                    
1654       1/1                          if (arbitration_lost_condition = '1') then
1655       1/1                              txtb_hw_cmd_d.unlock <= '1';
1656       1/1                              arbitration_lost_i <= '1';
1657       1/1                              stuff_enable_clear <= '1';
1658       1/1                              if (tx_failed = '1') then
1659       1/1                                  txtb_hw_cmd_d.failed  <= '1';
1660                                        else
1661       1/1                                  txtb_hw_cmd_d.arbl    <= '1';
1662                                        end if;
1663                                    end if;
1664                    
1665       1/1                          if (is_transmitter = '1' and tran_ident_type = BASE) then
1666       1/1                              if (tran_frame_type_i = FD_CAN or tran_is_rtr = NO_RTR_FRAME) then
1667       1/1                                  tx_dominant <= '1';
1668                                        end if;
1669                                    end if;
1670                    
1671       1/1                          if (tx_data_wbs = DOMINANT and rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE) then
1672       1/1                              bit_err_arb_i <= '1';
1673                                    end if;
1674                    
1675                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1676                                -- IDE bit
1677                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1678                                when s_pc_ide =>
1679       1/1                          tick_state_reg <= '1';
1680       1/1                          rx_store_ide_i <= '1';
1681       1/1                          crc_enable <= '1';
1682       1/1                          arbitration_part <= ALC_IDE;
1683                    
1684       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE) then
1685       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
1686       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_EXT_ID_DURATION;
1687       1/1                              tx_load_ext_id_i <= '1';
1688                                    end if;
1689                    
1690       1/1                          if (ide_is_arbitration = '1' and arbitration_lost_condition = '1') then
1691       1/1                              txtb_hw_cmd_d.unlock <= '1';
1692       1/1                              arbitration_lost_i <= '1';
1693       1/1                              stuff_enable_clear <= '1';
1694       1/1                              if (tx_failed = '1') then
1695       1/1                                  txtb_hw_cmd_d.failed  <= '1';
1696                                        else
1697       1/1                                  txtb_hw_cmd_d.arbl    <= '1';
1698                                        end if;
1699                                    end if;
1700                    
1701       1/1                          if (ide_is_arbitration = '1') then
1702       1/1                              is_arbitration_i <= '1';
1703       1/1                              bit_err_disable <= '1';
1704                                    else
1705       1/1                              pc_dbg.is_control <= '1';
1706                                    end if;
1707                    
1708       1/1                          if (tx_data_wbs = DOMINANT and rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE) then
1709       1/1                              bit_err_arb_i <= '1';
1710                                    end if;
1711                    
1712       1/1                          if (is_transmitter = '1' and tran_ident_type = BASE) then
1713       1/1                              tx_dominant <= '1';
1714                                    end if;
1715                    
1716       1/1                          if (ide_is_arbitration = '1') then
1717       1/1                              err_pos <= ERC_POS_ARB;
1718                                    else
1719       1/1                              err_pos <= ERC_POS_CTRL;
1720                                    end if;
1721                    
1722                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1723                                -- Extended identifier
1724                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1725                                when s_pc_ext_id =>
1726       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_ena <= '1';
1727       1/1                          rx_shift_ena <= "1111";
1728       1/1                          is_arbitration_i <= '1';
1729       1/1                          tx_shift_ena_i  <= '1';
1730       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_ARB;
1731       1/1                          bit_err_disable <= '1';
1732       1/1                          crc_enable <= '1';
1733       1/1                          arbitration_part <= ALC_EXTENSION;
1734                    
1735       1/1                          if (arbitration_lost_condition = '1') then
1736       1/1                              txtb_hw_cmd_d.unlock <= '1';
1737       1/1                              arbitration_lost_i <= '1';
1738       1/1                              stuff_enable_clear <= '1';
1739       1/1                              if (tx_failed = '1') then
1740       1/1                                  txtb_hw_cmd_d.failed  <= '1';
1741                                        else
1742       1/1                                  txtb_hw_cmd_d.arbl    <= '1';
1743                                        end if;
1744                                    end if;
1745                    
1746       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
1747       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
1748       1/1                              rx_store_ext_id_i         <= '1';
1749                                    end if;
1750                    
1751       1/1                          if (tx_data_wbs = DOMINANT and rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE) then
1752       1/1                              bit_err_arb_i <= '1';
1753                                    end if;
1754                    
1755                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1756                                -- RTR/R1 bit after the Extended identifier
1757                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1758                                when s_pc_rtr_r1 =>
1759       1/1                          tick_state_reg <= '1';
1760       1/1                          is_arbitration_i <= '1';
1761       1/1                          bit_err_disable <= '1';
1762       1/1                          crc_enable <= '1';
1763       1/1                          rx_store_rtr_i <= '1';
1764       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_ARB;
1765       1/1                          arbitration_part <= ALC_RTR;
1766                    
1767       1/1                          if (arbitration_lost_condition = '1') then
1768       1/1                              txtb_hw_cmd_d.unlock <= '1';
1769       1/1                              arbitration_lost_i <= '1';
1770       1/1                              stuff_enable_clear <= '1';
1771       1/1                              if (tx_failed = '1') then
1772       1/1                                  txtb_hw_cmd_d.failed  <= '1';
1773                                        else
1774       1/1                                  txtb_hw_cmd_d.arbl    <= '1';
1775                                        end if;
1776                                    end if;
1777                    
1778       1/1                          if (is_transmitter = '1') then
1779       1/1                              if (tran_frame_type_i = FD_CAN) then
1780       1/1                                  tx_dominant <= '1';
1781                                        elsif (tran_is_rtr = NO_RTR_FRAME) then
1782       1/1                                  tx_dominant <= '1';
1783                                        end if;
1784                                    end if;
1785                    
1786       1/1                          if (tx_data_wbs = DOMINANT and rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE) then
1787       1/1                              bit_err_arb_i <= '1';
1788                                    end if;
1789                    
1790                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1791                                -- EDL/r1 bit after RTR/r1 bit in Extended Identifier
1792                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1793                                when s_pc_edl_r1 =>
1794       1/1                          tick_state_reg <= '1';
1795       1/1                          rx_store_edl_i <= '1';
1796       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_CTRL;
1797       1/1                          crc_enable <= '1';
1798       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_control <= '1';
1799       1/1                          bit_err_disable_receiver <= '1';
1800                    
1801       1/1                          if (is_transmitter = '1') then
1802       1/1                              if (tran_frame_type_i = NORMAL_CAN) then
1803       1/1                                  tx_dominant <= '1';
1804                                        else
1805       1/1                                  ssp_reset_i <= '1';
1806                                        end if;
1807                                    end if;
1808                    
1809                                    -- Sample recessive but CAN FD is disabled -> Form error or protocol exception!
1810       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE and mr_mode_fde = FDE_DISABLE)
1811                                    then
1812       1/1                              if (mr_settings_pex = PROTOCOL_EXCEPTION_DISABLED) then
1813       1/1                                  form_err_i <= '1';
1814                    
1815                                        -- Detect protocol exception. Disable bit stuffing.
1816                                        else
1817       1/1                                  destuff_enable_clear <= '1';
1818       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
1819       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_INTEGRATION_DURATION;
1820       1/1                                  pexs_set <= '1';
1821                                        end if;
1822                                    end if;
1823                    
1824                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1825                                -- r0 bit after EDL/r1 bit in Extended CAN Frames.
1826                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1827                                when s_pc_r0_ext =>
1828       1/1                          tick_state_reg <= '1';
1829       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
1830       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_DLC_DURATION;
1831       1/1                          tx_load_dlc_i <= '1';
1832       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_CTRL;
1833       1/1                          tran_delay_meas <= '1';
1834       1/1                          crc_enable <= '1';
1835       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_control <= '1';
1836       1/1                          bit_err_disable_receiver <= '1';
1837                    
1838       1/1                          if (is_transmitter = '1') then
1839       1/1                              tx_dominant <= '1';
1840                                    end if;
1841                    
1842                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1843                                -- r0 bit in CAN FD Frames (both Base and Extended identifier)
1844                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1845                                when s_pc_r0_fd =>
1846       1/1                          tick_state_reg <= '1';
1847       1/1                          tran_delay_meas <= '1';
1848       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_CTRL;
1849       1/1                          perform_hsync <= '1';
1850       1/1                          crc_enable <= '1';
1851       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_control <= '1';
1852       1/1                          bit_err_disable_receiver <= '1';
1853                    
1854       1/1                          if (is_transmitter = '1') then
1855       1/1                              tx_dominant <= '1';
1856                                    end if;
1857                    
1858                                    -- Here recessive would mean further extending beyond CAN FD protocol (CAN XL in
1859                                    -- future). Now we don't have protocol exception, so we throw error here!
1860       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE) then
1861       1/1                              if (mr_settings_pex = PROTOCOL_EXCEPTION_DISABLED) then
1862       1/1                                  form_err_i <= '1';
1863                    
1864                                        -- Detect protocol exception. Disable bit stuffing.
1865                                        else
1866       1/1                                  destuff_enable_clear <= '1';
1867       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
1868       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_INTEGRATION_DURATION;
1869       1/1                                  pexs_set <= '1';
1870                                        end if;
1871                                    end if;
1872                    
1873                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1874                                -- EDL/r0 bit in CAN 2.0 and CAN FD Frames with BASE identifier only!
1875                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1876                                when s_pc_edl_r0 =>
1877       1/1                          tick_state_reg <= '1';
1878       1/1                          rx_store_edl_i <= '1';
1879       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_CTRL;
1880       1/1                          crc_enable <= '1';
1881       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_control <= '1';
1882       1/1                          bit_err_disable_receiver <= '1';
1883                    
1884       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
1885       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
1886       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_DLC_DURATION;
1887       1/1                              tx_load_dlc_i <= '1';
1888                                    end if;
1889                    
1890       1/1                          if (is_transmitter = '1' and tran_frame_type_i = NORMAL_CAN) then
1891       1/1                              tx_dominant <= '1';
1892                                    else
1893       1/1                              ssp_reset_i <= '1';
1894                                    end if;
1895                    
1896                                    -- Sample recessive but CAN FD is disabled -> Form error or
1897                                    -- protocol exception!
1898       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE and mr_mode_fde = FDE_DISABLE) then
1899       1/1                              if (mr_settings_pex = PROTOCOL_EXCEPTION_DISABLED) then
1900       1/1                                  form_err_i <= '1';
1901                    
1902                                        -- Detect protocol exception. Disable bit stuffing.
1903                                        else
1904       1/1                                  destuff_enable_clear <= '1';
1905       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
1906       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_INTEGRATION_DURATION;
1907       1/1                                  pexs_set <= '1';
1908                                        end if;
1909                                    end if;
1910                    
1911                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1912                                -- BRS (Bit rate shift) Bit
1913                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1914                                when s_pc_brs =>
1915       1/1                          tick_state_reg <= '1';
1916       1/1                          rx_store_brs_i <= '1';
1917       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_CTRL;
1918       1/1                          crc_enable <= '1';
1919       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_control <= '1';
1920       1/1                          bit_err_disable_receiver <= '1';
1921       1/1                          dbt_ctrs_en <= '1';
1922       1/1                          btmc_reset  <= '1';
1923                    
1924       1/1                          if (is_transmitter = '1' and tran_brs = BR_NO_SHIFT) then
1925       1/1                              tx_dominant <= '1';
1926                                    end if;
1927                    
1928       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE and rx_trigger = '1') then
1929       1/1                              sp_control_switch_data <= '1';
1930       1/1                              br_shifted_i <= '1';
1931                                    end if;
1932                    
1933                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1934                                -- ESI (Error State Indicator) Bit
1935                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1936                                when s_pc_esi =>
1937       1/1                          tick_state_reg <= '1';
1938       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
1939       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_DLC_DURATION;
1940       1/1                          tx_load_dlc_i <= '1';
1941       1/1                          rx_store_esi_i <= '1';
1942       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_CTRL;
1943       1/1                          crc_enable <= '1';
1944       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_control <= '1';
1945       1/1                          bit_err_disable_receiver <= '1';
1946       1/1                          dbt_ctrs_en <= '1';
1947                    
1948       1/1                          if (is_transmitter = '1' and is_err_active = '1') then
1949       1/1                              tx_dominant <= '1';
1950                                    end if;
1951                    
1952                                    -- Transmitter transmitts via SSP
1953       1/1                          if (sp_control_q_i = SECONDARY_SAMPLE) then
1954       1/1                              dbt_measure_start <= '1';
1955       1/1                              gen_first_ssp     <= '1';
1956                                    end if;
1957                    
1958                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1959                                -- DLC (Data length code)
1960                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1961                                when s_pc_dlc =>
1962       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_ena <= '1';
1963       1/1                          rx_shift_ena <= "1111";
1964       1/1                          tx_shift_ena_i  <= '1';
1965       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_CTRL;
1966       1/1                          crc_enable <= '1';
1967       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_control <= '1';
1968       1/1                          bit_err_disable_receiver <= '1';
1969                    
1970       1/1                          if (sp_control_q_i /= NOMINAL_SAMPLE) then
1971       1/1                              dbt_ctrs_en <= '1';
1972                                    end if;
1973                    
1974                                    -- Address first Data Word in TXT Buffer RAM in advance to account for DFF delay
1975                                    -- and RAM delay! Do it only when transmitting to avoid toggling of RAM signals
1976                                    -- during reception (possible power consideration)
1977       1/1                          if (is_transmitter = '1') then
1978       1/1                              txtb_ptr_d <= 4;
1979                                    end if;
1980                    
1981       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
1982       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
1983       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
1984                    
1985       1/1                              if (no_data_field = '1') then
1986       1/1                                  if (go_to_stuff_count = '1') then
1987       1/1                                      ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_STUFF_COUNT_DURATION;
1988       1/1                                      tx_load_stuff_count_i <= '1';
1989                                            else
1990       1/1                                      ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= crc_length_i;
1991       1/1                                      tx_load_crc_i <= '1';
1992                                            end if;
1993                                        else
1994       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= data_length_bits_c;
1995       1/1                                  tx_load_data_word_i <= '1';
1996                                        end if;
1997                    
1998       1/1                              store_metadata_d <= '1';
1999       1/1                              rx_store_dlc_i <= '1';
2000                                    end if;
2001                    
2002                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2003                                -- Data field
2004                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2005                                when s_pc_data =>
2006       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_ena <= '1';
2007       1/1                          rx_shift_ena(to_integer(unsigned(ctrl_counted_byte_index))) <= '1';
2008       1/1                          rx_shift_in_sel <= '1';
2009       1/1                          tx_shift_ena_i <= '1';
2010       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_DATA;
2011       1/1                          crc_enable <= '1';
2012       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_data <= '1';
2013       1/1                          compl_ctr_ena_i <= '1';
2014       1/1                          bit_err_disable_receiver <= '1';
2015                    
2016       1/1                          if (sp_control_q_i /= NOMINAL_SAMPLE) then
2017       1/1                              dbt_ctrs_en <= '1';
2018                                    end if;
2019                    
2020                                    -- Address next word (the one after actually transmitted one), so that when current
2021                                    -- word ends, TXT Buffer RAM already provides data on its output! Counter is divided
2022                                    -- by 32 since each memory word contains 32 bits!
2023       1/1                          if (is_transmitter = '1') then
2024       1/1                              txtb_ptr_d <= to_integer(unsigned(ctrl_ctr_mem_index));
2025                                    end if;
2026                    
2027       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
2028       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
2029       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
2030                    
2031       1/1                              if (go_to_stuff_count = '1') then
2032       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_STUFF_COUNT_DURATION;
2033       1/1                                  tx_load_stuff_count_i <= '1';
2034                                        else
2035       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= crc_length_i;
2036       1/1                                  tx_load_crc_i <= '1';
2037                                        end if;
2038                    
2039                                        -- Store data word at the end of data field.
2040       1/1                              store_data_d <= '1';
2041                                    end if;
2042                    
2043                                    -- Store data word when multiple of 4 data bytes were counted! Avoid storing at the
2044                                    -- end of Data field, because CRC must be preloaded then!
2045       1/1                          if (ctrl_counted_byte = '1' and
2046                                        ctrl_counted_byte_index = "11" and
2047                                        ctrl_ctr_zero = '0')
2048                                    then
2049       1/1                              store_data_d <= '1';
2050       1/1                              tx_load_data_word_i <= '1';
2051                                    end if;
2052                    
2053                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2054                                -- Stuff count + Stuff parity field
2055                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2056                                when s_pc_stuff_count =>
2057       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_ena <= '1';
2058       1/1                          rx_shift_ena <= "1111";
2059       1/1                          tx_shift_ena_i <= '1';
2060       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_CRC;
2061       1/1                          crc_enable <= '1';
2062       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_stuff_count <= '1';
2063       1/1                          bit_err_disable_receiver <= '1';
2064                    
2065       1/1                          if (sp_control_q_i /= NOMINAL_SAMPLE) then
2066       1/1                              dbt_ctrs_en <= '1';
2067                                    end if;
2068                    
2069       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
2070       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
2071       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= crc_length_i;
2072       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
2073       1/1                              tx_load_crc_i <= '1';
2074       1/1                              rx_store_stuff_count_i <= '1';
2075                                    end if;
2076                    
2077       1/1                          if (is_fd_frame = '1') then
2078       1/1                              stuff_length <= std_logic_vector(to_unsigned(4, 3));
2079       1/1                              fixed_stuff <= '1';
2080                                    end if;
2081                    
2082                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2083                                -- CRC field
2084                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2085                                when s_pc_crc =>
2086       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_ena <= '1';
2087       1/1                          rx_shift_ena <= "1111";
2088       1/1                          tx_shift_ena_i <= '1';
2089       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_CRC;
2090       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_crc <= '1';
2091       1/1                          bit_err_disable_receiver <= '1';
2092                    
2093       1/1                          if (sp_control_q_i /= NOMINAL_SAMPLE) then
2094       1/1                              dbt_ctrs_en <= '1';
2095                                    end if;
2096                    
2097       1/1                          if (is_fd_frame = '1') then
2098       1/1                              stuff_length <= std_logic_vector(to_unsigned(4, 3));
2099       1/1                              fixed_stuff <= '1';
2100                                    end if;
2101                    
2102       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
2103       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
2104                                    end if;
2105                    
2106                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2107                                -- CRC Delimiter
2108                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2109                                when s_pc_crc_delim =>
2110       1/1                          tick_state_reg <= '1';
2111       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_ACK;
2112       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_crc_delim  <= '1';
2113       1/1                          dbt_ctrs_en <= '1';
2114       1/1                          bit_err_disable <= '1';
2115       1/1                          destuff_enable_clear <= '1';
2116       1/1                          stuff_enable_clear <= '1';
2117                    
2118       1/1                          if (rx_trigger = '1') then
2119       1/1                              if (is_receiver = '1') then
2120       1/1                                  crc_check <= '1';
2121                                        end if;
2122                    
2123       1/1                              if (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
2124       1/1                                  form_err_i <= '1';
2125                                        end if;
2126                    
2127       1/1                              if (sp_control_q_i = DATA_SAMPLE or sp_control_q_i = SECONDARY_SAMPLE) then
2128       1/1                                  sp_control_switch_nominal <= '1';
2129       1/1                                  br_shifted_i <= '1';
2130                                        end if;
2131                                    end if;
2132                    
2133                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2134                                -- ACK Slot of CAN 2.0 frame
2135                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2136                                when s_pc_ack =>
2137       1/1                          tick_state_reg <= '1';
2138       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_ACK;
2139       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_ack <= '1';
2140       1/1                          dbt_ctrs_en <= '1';
2141                    
2142       1/1                          if (is_receiver = '1' and crc_match = '1' and mr_mode_acf = '0') then
2143       1/1                              tx_dominant <= '1';
2144                    
2145                                    -- Bit Error still shall be detected when unit sends dominant
2146                                    -- (receiver) and receives recessive!
2147                                    else
2148       1/1                              bit_err_disable <= '1';
2149                                    end if;
2150                    
2151       1/1                          if (is_receiver = '1' and crc_match = '1' and rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
2152       1/1                              decrement_rec_i <= '1';
2153                                    end if;
2154                    
2155       1/1                          if (is_transmitter = '1' and mr_mode_stm = '0' and rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE) then
2156       1/1                              ack_err_i <= '1';
2157                                    end if;
2158                    
2159                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2160                                -- First bit of CAN FD Frame ACK - Receiver sends ACK
2161                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2162                                when s_pc_ack_fd_1 =>
2163       1/1                          tick_state_reg <= '1';
2164       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_ACK;
2165       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_ack <= '1';
2166       1/1                          dbt_ctrs_en <= '1';
2167                    
2168       1/1                          if (is_receiver = '1' and crc_match = '1' and mr_mode_acf = '0') then
2169       1/1                              tx_dominant <= '1';
2170                    
2171                                    -- Bit Error still shall be detected when unit sends dominant
2172                                    -- (receiver) and receives recessive!
2173                                    else
2174       1/1                              bit_err_disable <= '1';
2175                                    end if;
2176                    
2177       1/1                          if (is_receiver = '1' and crc_match = '1' and rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
2178       1/1                              decrement_rec_i <= '1';
2179                                    end if;
2180                    
2181                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2182                                -- Second bit of CAN FD Frame ACK
2183                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2184                                when s_pc_ack_fd_2 =>
2185       1/1                          tick_state_reg <= '1';
2186       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_ACK;
2187       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_ack <= '1';
2188       1/1                          dbt_ctrs_en <= '1';
2189                    
2190                                    -- No ACK sent now, but dominant or recessive should be tolerated.
2191       1/1                          bit_err_disable <= '1';
2192                    
2193                                    -- Transmitter not detecting dominant bit now, nor at previous bit -> Ack Error
2194       1/1                          if (is_transmitter = '1' and mr_mode_stm = '0' and
2195                                        rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE and rx_data_nbs_prev = RECESSIVE)
2196                                    then
2197       1/1                              ack_err_i <= '1';
2198                                    end if;
2199                    
2200                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2201                                -- ACK Delimiter
