1719       1/1                              err_pos <= ERC_POS_CTRL;
1720                                    end if;
1721                    
1722                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1723                                -- Extended identifier
1724                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1725                                when s_pc_ext_id =>
1726       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_ena <= '1';
1727       1/1                          rx_shift_ena <= "1111";
1728       1/1                          is_arbitration_i <= '1';
1729       1/1                          tx_shift_ena_i  <= '1';
1730       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_ARB;
1731       1/1                          bit_err_disable <= '1';
1732       1/1                          crc_enable <= '1';
1733       1/1                          arbitration_part <= ALC_EXTENSION;
1734                    
1735       1/1                          if (arbitration_lost_condition = '1') then
1736       1/1                              txtb_hw_cmd_d.unlock <= '1';
1737       1/1                              arbitration_lost_i <= '1';
1738       1/1                              stuff_enable_clear <= '1';
1739       1/1                              if (tx_failed = '1') then
1740       1/1                                  txtb_hw_cmd_d.failed  <= '1';
1741                                        else
1742       1/1                                  txtb_hw_cmd_d.arbl    <= '1';
1743                                        end if;
1744                                    end if;
1745                    
1746       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
1747       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
1748       1/1                              rx_store_ext_id_i         <= '1';
1749                                    end if;
1750                    
1751       1/1                          if (tx_data_wbs = DOMINANT and rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE) then
1752       1/1                              bit_err_arb_i <= '1';
1753                                    end if;
1754                    
1755                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1756                                -- RTR/R1 bit after the Extended identifier
1757                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1758                                when s_pc_rtr_r1 =>
1759       1/1                          tick_state_reg <= '1';
1760       1/1                          is_arbitration_i <= '1';
1761       1/1                          bit_err_disable <= '1';
1762       1/1                          crc_enable <= '1';
1763       1/1                          rx_store_rtr_i <= '1';
1764       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_ARB;
1765       1/1                          arbitration_part <= ALC_RTR;
1766                    
1767       1/1                          if (arbitration_lost_condition = '1') then
1768       1/1                              txtb_hw_cmd_d.unlock <= '1';
1769       1/1                              arbitration_lost_i <= '1';
1770       1/1                              stuff_enable_clear <= '1';
1771       1/1                              if (tx_failed = '1') then
1772       1/1                                  txtb_hw_cmd_d.failed  <= '1';
1773                                        else
1774       1/1                                  txtb_hw_cmd_d.arbl    <= '1';
1775                                        end if;
1776                                    end if;
1777                    
1778       1/1                          if (is_transmitter = '1') then
1779       1/1                              if (tran_frame_type_i = FD_CAN) then
1780       1/1                                  tx_dominant <= '1';
1781                                        elsif (tran_is_rtr = NO_RTR_FRAME) then
1782       1/1                                  tx_dominant <= '1';
1783                                        end if;
1784                                    end if;
1785                    
1786       1/1                          if (tx_data_wbs = DOMINANT and rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE) then
1787       1/1                              bit_err_arb_i <= '1';
1788                                    end if;
1789                    
1790                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1791                                -- EDL/r1 bit after RTR/r1 bit in Extended Identifier
1792                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1793                                when s_pc_edl_r1 =>
1794       1/1                          tick_state_reg <= '1';
1795       1/1                          rx_store_edl_i <= '1';
1796       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_CTRL;
1797       1/1                          crc_enable <= '1';
1798       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_control <= '1';
1799       1/1                          bit_err_disable_receiver <= '1';
1800                    
1801       1/1                          if (is_transmitter = '1') then
1802       1/1                              if (tran_frame_type_i = NORMAL_CAN) then
1803       1/1                                  tx_dominant <= '1';
1804                                        else
1805       1/1                                  ssp_reset_i <= '1';
1806                                        end if;
1807                                    end if;
1808                    
1809                                    -- Sample recessive but CAN FD is disabled -> Form error or protocol exception!
1810       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE and mr_mode_fde = FDE_DISABLE)
1811                                    then
1812       1/1                              if (mr_settings_pex = PROTOCOL_EXCEPTION_DISABLED) then
1813       1/1                                  form_err_i <= '1';
1814                    
1815                                        -- Detect protocol exception. Disable bit stuffing.
1816                                        else
1817       1/1                                  destuff_enable_clear <= '1';
1818       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
1819       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_INTEGRATION_DURATION;
1820       1/1                                  pexs_set <= '1';
1821                                        end if;
1822                                    end if;
1823                    
1824                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1825                                -- r0 bit after EDL/r1 bit in Extended CAN Frames.
1826                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1827                                when s_pc_r0_ext =>
1828       1/1                          tick_state_reg <= '1';
1829       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
1830       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_DLC_DURATION;
1831       1/1                          tx_load_dlc_i <= '1';
1832       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_CTRL;
1833       1/1                          tran_delay_meas <= '1';
1834       1/1                          crc_enable <= '1';
1835       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_control <= '1';
1836       1/1                          bit_err_disable_receiver <= '1';
1837                    
1838       1/1                          if (is_transmitter = '1') then
1839       1/1                              tx_dominant <= '1';
1840                                    end if;
1841                    
1842                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1843                                -- r0 bit in CAN FD Frames (both Base and Extended identifier)
1844                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1845                                when s_pc_r0_fd =>
1846       1/1                          tick_state_reg <= '1';
1847       1/1                          tran_delay_meas <= '1';
1848       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_CTRL;
1849       1/1                          perform_hsync <= '1';
1850       1/1                          crc_enable <= '1';
1851       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_control <= '1';
1852       1/1                          bit_err_disable_receiver <= '1';
1853                    
1854       1/1                          if (is_transmitter = '1') then
1855       1/1                              tx_dominant <= '1';
1856                                    end if;
1857                    
1858                                    -- Here recessive would mean further extending beyond CAN FD protocol (CAN XL in
1859                                    -- future). Now we don't have protocol exception, so we throw error here!
1860       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE) then
1861       1/1                              if (mr_settings_pex = PROTOCOL_EXCEPTION_DISABLED) then
1862       1/1                                  form_err_i <= '1';
1863                    
1864                                        -- Detect protocol exception. Disable bit stuffing.
1865                                        else
1866       1/1                                  destuff_enable_clear <= '1';
1867       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
1868       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_INTEGRATION_DURATION;
1869       1/1                                  pexs_set <= '1';
1870                                        end if;
1871                                    end if;
1872                    
1873                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1874                                -- EDL/r0 bit in CAN 2.0 and CAN FD Frames with BASE identifier only!
1875                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1876                                when s_pc_edl_r0 =>
1877       1/1                          tick_state_reg <= '1';
1878       1/1                          rx_store_edl_i <= '1';
1879       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_CTRL;
1880       1/1                          crc_enable <= '1';
1881       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_control <= '1';
1882       1/1                          bit_err_disable_receiver <= '1';
1883                    
1884       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
1885       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
1886       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_DLC_DURATION;
1887       1/1                              tx_load_dlc_i <= '1';
1888                                    end if;
1889                    
1890       1/1                          if (is_transmitter = '1' and tran_frame_type_i = NORMAL_CAN) then
1891       1/1                              tx_dominant <= '1';
1892                                    else
1893       1/1                              ssp_reset_i <= '1';
1894                                    end if;
1895                    
1896                                    -- Sample recessive but CAN FD is disabled -> Form error or
1897                                    -- protocol exception!
1898       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE and mr_mode_fde = FDE_DISABLE) then
1899       1/1                              if (mr_settings_pex = PROTOCOL_EXCEPTION_DISABLED) then
1900       1/1                                  form_err_i <= '1';
1901                    
1902                                        -- Detect protocol exception. Disable bit stuffing.
1903                                        else
1904       1/1                                  destuff_enable_clear <= '1';
1905       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
1906       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_INTEGRATION_DURATION;
1907       1/1                                  pexs_set <= '1';
1908                                        end if;
1909                                    end if;
1910                    
1911                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1912                                -- BRS (Bit rate shift) Bit
1913                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1914                                when s_pc_brs =>
1915       1/1                          tick_state_reg <= '1';
1916       1/1                          rx_store_brs_i <= '1';
1917       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_CTRL;
1918       1/1                          crc_enable <= '1';
1919       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_control <= '1';
1920       1/1                          bit_err_disable_receiver <= '1';
1921       1/1                          dbt_ctrs_en <= '1';
1922       1/1                          btmc_reset  <= '1';
1923                    
1924       1/1                          if (is_transmitter = '1' and tran_brs = BR_NO_SHIFT) then
1925       1/1                              tx_dominant <= '1';
1926                                    end if;
1927                    
1928       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE and rx_trigger = '1') then
1929       1/1                              sp_control_switch_data <= '1';
1930       1/1                              br_shifted_i <= '1';
1931                                    end if;
1932                    
1933                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1934                                -- ESI (Error State Indicator) Bit
1935                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1936                                when s_pc_esi =>
1937       1/1                          tick_state_reg <= '1';
1938       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
1939       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_DLC_DURATION;
1940       1/1                          tx_load_dlc_i <= '1';
1941       1/1                          rx_store_esi_i <= '1';
1942       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_CTRL;
1943       1/1                          crc_enable <= '1';
1944       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_control <= '1';
1945       1/1                          bit_err_disable_receiver <= '1';
1946       1/1                          dbt_ctrs_en <= '1';
1947                    
1948       1/1                          if (is_transmitter = '1' and is_err_active = '1') then
1949       1/1                              tx_dominant <= '1';
1950                                    end if;
1951                    
1952                                    -- Transmitter transmitts via SSP
1953       1/1                          if (sp_control_q_i = SECONDARY_SAMPLE) then
1954       1/1                              dbt_measure_start <= '1';
1955       1/1                              gen_first_ssp     <= '1';
1956                                    end if;
1957                    
1958                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1959                                -- DLC (Data length code)
1960                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1961                                when s_pc_dlc =>
1962       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_ena <= '1';
1963       1/1                          rx_shift_ena <= "1111";
1964       1/1                          tx_shift_ena_i  <= '1';
1965       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_CTRL;
1966       1/1                          crc_enable <= '1';
1967       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_control <= '1';
1968       1/1                          bit_err_disable_receiver <= '1';
1969                    
1970       1/1                          if (sp_control_q_i /= NOMINAL_SAMPLE) then
1971       1/1                              dbt_ctrs_en <= '1';
1972                                    end if;
1973                    
1974                                    -- Address first Data Word in TXT Buffer RAM in advance to account for DFF delay
1975                                    -- and RAM delay! Do it only when transmitting to avoid toggling of RAM signals
1976                                    -- during reception (possible power consideration)
1977       1/1                          if (is_transmitter = '1') then
1978       1/1                              txtb_ptr_d <= 4;
1979                                    end if;
1980                    
1981       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
1982       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
1983       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
1984                    
1985       1/1                              if (no_data_field = '1') then
1986       1/1                                  if (go_to_stuff_count = '1') then
1987       1/1                                      ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_STUFF_COUNT_DURATION;
1988       1/1                                      tx_load_stuff_count_i <= '1';
1989                                            else
1990       1/1                                      ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= crc_length_i;
1991       1/1                                      tx_load_crc_i <= '1';
1992                                            end if;
1993                                        else
1994       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= data_length_bits_c;
1995       1/1                                  tx_load_data_word_i <= '1';
1996                                        end if;
1997                    
1998       1/1                              store_metadata_d <= '1';
1999       1/1                              rx_store_dlc_i <= '1';
2000                                    end if;
2001                    
2002                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2003                                -- Data field
2004                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2005                                when s_pc_data =>
2006       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_ena <= '1';
2007       1/1                          rx_shift_ena(to_integer(unsigned(ctrl_counted_byte_index))) <= '1';
2008       1/1                          rx_shift_in_sel <= '1';
2009       1/1                          tx_shift_ena_i <= '1';
2010       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_DATA;
2011       1/1                          crc_enable <= '1';
2012       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_data <= '1';
2013       1/1                          compl_ctr_ena_i <= '1';
2014       1/1                          bit_err_disable_receiver <= '1';
2015                    
2016       1/1                          if (sp_control_q_i /= NOMINAL_SAMPLE) then
2017       1/1                              dbt_ctrs_en <= '1';
2018                                    end if;
2019                    
2020                                    -- Address next word (the one after actually transmitted one), so that when current
2021                                    -- word ends, TXT Buffer RAM already provides data on its output! Counter is divided
2022                                    -- by 32 since each memory word contains 32 bits!
2023       1/1                          if (is_transmitter = '1') then
2024       1/1                              txtb_ptr_d <= to_integer(unsigned(ctrl_ctr_mem_index));
2025                                    end if;
2026                    
2027       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
2028       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
2029       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
2030                    
2031       1/1                              if (go_to_stuff_count = '1') then
2032       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_STUFF_COUNT_DURATION;
2033       1/1                                  tx_load_stuff_count_i <= '1';
2034                                        else
2035       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= crc_length_i;
2036       1/1                                  tx_load_crc_i <= '1';
2037                                        end if;
2038                    
2039                                        -- Store data word at the end of data field.
2040       1/1                              store_data_d <= '1';
2041                                    end if;
2042                    
2043                                    -- Store data word when multiple of 4 data bytes were counted! Avoid storing at the
2044                                    -- end of Data field, because CRC must be preloaded then!
2045       1/1                          if (ctrl_counted_byte = '1' and
2046                                        ctrl_counted_byte_index = "11" and
2047                                        ctrl_ctr_zero = '0')
2048                                    then
2049       1/1                              store_data_d <= '1';
2050       1/1                              tx_load_data_word_i <= '1';
2051                                    end if;
2052                    
2053                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2054                                -- Stuff count + Stuff parity field
2055                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2056                                when s_pc_stuff_count =>
2057       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_ena <= '1';
2058       1/1                          rx_shift_ena <= "1111";
2059       1/1                          tx_shift_ena_i <= '1';
2060       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_CRC;
2061       1/1                          crc_enable <= '1';
2062       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_stuff_count <= '1';
2063       1/1                          bit_err_disable_receiver <= '1';
2064                    
2065       1/1                          if (sp_control_q_i /= NOMINAL_SAMPLE) then
2066       1/1                              dbt_ctrs_en <= '1';
2067                                    end if;
2068                    
2069       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
2070       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
2071       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= crc_length_i;
2072       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
2073       1/1                              tx_load_crc_i <= '1';
2074       1/1                              rx_store_stuff_count_i <= '1';
2075                                    end if;
2076                    
2077       1/1                          if (is_fd_frame = '1') then
2078       1/1                              stuff_length <= std_logic_vector(to_unsigned(4, 3));
2079       1/1                              fixed_stuff <= '1';
2080                                    end if;
2081                    
2082                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2083                                -- CRC field
2084                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2085                                when s_pc_crc =>
2086       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_ena <= '1';
2087       1/1                          rx_shift_ena <= "1111";
2088       1/1                          tx_shift_ena_i <= '1';
2089       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_CRC;
2090       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_crc <= '1';
2091       1/1                          bit_err_disable_receiver <= '1';
2092                    
2093       1/1                          if (sp_control_q_i /= NOMINAL_SAMPLE) then
2094       1/1                              dbt_ctrs_en <= '1';
2095                                    end if;
2096                    
2097       1/1                          if (is_fd_frame = '1') then
2098       1/1                              stuff_length <= std_logic_vector(to_unsigned(4, 3));
2099       1/1                              fixed_stuff <= '1';
2100                                    end if;
2101                    
2102       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
2103       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
2104                                    end if;
2105                    
2106                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2107                                -- CRC Delimiter
2108                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2109                                when s_pc_crc_delim =>
2110       1/1                          tick_state_reg <= '1';
2111       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_ACK;
2112       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_crc_delim  <= '1';
2113       1/1                          dbt_ctrs_en <= '1';
2114       1/1                          bit_err_disable <= '1';
2115       1/1                          destuff_enable_clear <= '1';
2116       1/1                          stuff_enable_clear <= '1';
2117                    
2118       1/1                          if (rx_trigger = '1') then
2119       1/1                              if (is_receiver = '1') then
2120       1/1                                  crc_check <= '1';
2121                                        end if;
2122                    
2123       1/1                              if (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
2124       1/1                                  form_err_i <= '1';
2125                                        end if;
2126                    
2127       1/1                              if (sp_control_q_i = DATA_SAMPLE or sp_control_q_i = SECONDARY_SAMPLE) then
2128       1/1                                  sp_control_switch_nominal <= '1';
2129       1/1                                  br_shifted_i <= '1';
2130                                        end if;
2131                                    end if;
2132                    
2133                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2134                                -- ACK Slot of CAN 2.0 frame
2135                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2136                                when s_pc_ack =>
2137       1/1                          tick_state_reg <= '1';
2138       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_ACK;
2139       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_ack <= '1';
2140       1/1                          dbt_ctrs_en <= '1';
2141                    
2142       1/1                          if (is_receiver = '1' and crc_match = '1' and mr_mode_acf = '0') then
2143       1/1                              tx_dominant <= '1';
2144                    
2145                                    -- Bit Error still shall be detected when unit sends dominant
2146                                    -- (receiver) and receives recessive!
2147                                    else
2148       1/1                              bit_err_disable <= '1';
2149                                    end if;
2150                    
2151       1/1                          if (is_receiver = '1' and crc_match = '1' and rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
2152       1/1                              decrement_rec_i <= '1';
2153                                    end if;
2154                    
2155       1/1                          if (is_transmitter = '1' and mr_mode_stm = '0' and rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE) then
2156       1/1                              ack_err_i <= '1';
2157                                    end if;
2158                    
2159                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2160                                -- First bit of CAN FD Frame ACK - Receiver sends ACK
2161                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2162                                when s_pc_ack_fd_1 =>
2163       1/1                          tick_state_reg <= '1';
2164       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_ACK;
2165       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_ack <= '1';
2166       1/1                          dbt_ctrs_en <= '1';
2167                    
2168       1/1                          if (is_receiver = '1' and crc_match = '1' and mr_mode_acf = '0') then
2169       1/1                              tx_dominant <= '1';
2170                    
2171                                    -- Bit Error still shall be detected when unit sends dominant
2172                                    -- (receiver) and receives recessive!
2173                                    else
2174       1/1                              bit_err_disable <= '1';
2175                                    end if;
2176                    
2177       1/1                          if (is_receiver = '1' and crc_match = '1' and rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
2178       1/1                              decrement_rec_i <= '1';
2179                                    end if;
2180                    
2181                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2182                                -- Second bit of CAN FD Frame ACK
2183                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2184                                when s_pc_ack_fd_2 =>
2185       1/1                          tick_state_reg <= '1';
2186       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_ACK;
2187       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_ack <= '1';
2188       1/1                          dbt_ctrs_en <= '1';
2189                    
2190                                    -- No ACK sent now, but dominant or recessive should be tolerated.
2191       1/1                          bit_err_disable <= '1';
2192                    
2193                                    -- Transmitter not detecting dominant bit now, nor at previous bit -> Ack Error
2194       1/1                          if (is_transmitter = '1' and mr_mode_stm = '0' and
2195                                        rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE and rx_data_nbs_prev = RECESSIVE)
2196                                    then
2197       1/1                              ack_err_i <= '1';
2198                                    end if;
2199                    
2200                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2201                                -- ACK Delimiter
2202                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2203                                when s_pc_ack_delim =>
2204       1/1                          tick_state_reg <= '1';
2205       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
2206       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_EOF_DURATION;
2207       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_ACK;
2208       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_ack_delim  <= '1';
2209       1/1                          bit_err_disable <= '1';
2210                    
2211       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
2212       1/1                              form_err_i <= '1';
2213                                    end if;
2214                    
2215       1/1                          if (is_receiver = '1' and crc_match = '0') then
2216       1/1                              crc_err_i <= '1';
2217                                    end if;
2218                    
2219                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2220                                -- End of Frame. Receiver sampling DOMINANT in last bit interprets this as Overload
2221                                -- flag!
2222                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2223                                when s_pc_eof =>
2224       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_ena <= '1';
2225       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_eof <= '1';
2226       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_EOF;
2227       1/1                          bit_err_disable <= '1';
2228                    
2229       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
2230       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
2231       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
2232                    
2233       1/1                              if (rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE) then
2234       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_INTERMISSION_DURATION;
2235                    
2236                                            -- No Error until the end of EOF means frame is valid for transmitter!
2237       1/1                                  if (is_transmitter = '1') then
2238       1/1                                      txtb_hw_cmd_d.unlock <= '1';
2239       1/1                                      txtb_hw_cmd_d.valid  <= '1';
2240                                            end if;
2241                    
2242                                        elsif (is_receiver = '1') then
2243       1/1                                  if (mr_mode_rom = ROM_DISABLED) then
2244       1/1                                      ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_OVR_FLG_DURATION;
2245                                            else
2246       1/1                                      ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_INTEGRATION_DURATION;
2247       1/1                                      set_idle_i <= '1';
2248                                            end if;
2249                                        end if;
2250                    
2251       1/1                              crc_clear_match_flag <= '1';
2252                                    end if;
2253                    
2254                                    -- If there is no error (RX Recessive) in one bit before end of EOF, signal valid
2255                                    -- Frame reception!
2256       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_one = '1' and rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE) then
2257       1/1                              rec_valid_d <= '1';
2258                                    end if;
2259                    
2260                                    -- DOMINANT during EOF. All bits before last -> Form error! Last bit -> Receiver
2261                                    -- treats it as overload condition, so no error frame will be transmitted.
2262                                    -- Transmitter treats it as Form error!
2263       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
2264       1/1                              if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '0') then
2265       1/1                                  form_err_i <= '1';
2266                                        elsif (is_transmitter = '1') then
2267       1/1                                  form_err_i <= '1';
2268                                        end if;
2269                                    end if;
2270                    
2271                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2272                                -- Intermission field
2273                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2274                                when s_pc_intermission =>
2275       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_ena <= '1';
2276       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_intermission <= '1';
2277       1/1                          retr_ctr_add_block_clr <= '1';
2278       1/1                          bit_err_disable <= '1';
2279                    
2280                                    -- If we are bus-off, go to reintegration wait!
2281       1/1                          if (is_bus_off = '1') then
2282       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
2283                                    end if;
2284                    
2285                                    -- Last (third) bit of intermission
2286       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1' and is_bus_off = '0') then
2287       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
2288       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
2289       1/1                              crc_spec_enable_i <= '1';
2290                    
2291                                        -- Goe to Base ID (sampling of DOMINANT in the third bit of intermission)!
2292       1/1                              if (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
2293       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_BASE_ID_DURATION;
2294       1/1                                  tx_load_base_id_i <= '1';
2295       1/1                                  sof_pulse_i <= '1';
2296                    
2297                                        -- Goes to either IDLE, Suspend, or to SOF, when there is sth. to transmitt.
2298                                        -- Preload SUSPEND length in any case, since other states don't care about
2299                                        -- control counter.
2300                                        else
2301       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_SUSPEND_DURATION;
2302                                        end if;
2303                    
2304                                        -- Lock TXT Buffer when there is what to transmitt, and no suspend! Unit becomes
2305                                        -- transmitter! If not, and DOMINANT is received, become receiver!
2306       1/1                              if (tx_frame_ready = '1' and go_to_suspend = '0') then
2307       1/1                                  txtb_hw_cmd_d.lock <= '1';
2308       1/1                                  set_transmitter_i <= '1';
2309       1/1                                  stuff_enable_set <= '1';
2310                    
2311       1/1                                  if (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
2312       1/1                                      tx_frame_no_sof_d <= '1';
2313                                            end if;
2314                    
2315                                        elsif (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
2316       1/1                                  set_receiver_i   <= '1';
2317                                        end if;
2318                    
2319                                        -- Transmission/reception started -> Enable Bit stuffing! Clear RX Shift
2320                                        -- Register!
2321       1/1                              if (frame_start = '1') then
2322       1/1                                  destuff_enable_set <= '1';
2323       1/1                                  rx_clear_i <= '1';
2324                                        end if;
2325                    
2326                                        -- If we dont sample dominant, nor we have sth ready for transmission, we go to
2327                                        -- Idle! Don't become idle when we go to suspend!
2328       1/1                              if (rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE and tx_frame_ready = '0' and
2329                                            go_to_suspend = '0')
2330                                        then
2331       1/1                                  set_idle_i <= '1';
2332                                        end if;
2333                    
2334                                    -- First or second bit of intermission!
2335                                    elsif (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT and is_bus_off = '0') then
2336       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
2337       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
2338       1/1                              if (mr_mode_rom = ROM_DISABLED) then
2339       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_OVR_FLG_DURATION;
2340                                        else
2341       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_INTEGRATION_DURATION;
2342       1/1                                  set_idle_i <= '1';
2343                                        end if;
2344                                    end if;
2345                    
2346                                    -- Second or third bit of intermission, Hard Synchronisation
2347       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1' or ctrl_ctr_one = '1') then
2348       1/1                              perform_hsync <= '1';
2349                                    end if;
2350                    
2351                                    -- First or second bit of Intermission, pre-load CRC Init vector for next frame.
2352       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '0') then
2353       1/1                              load_init_vect_i <= '1';
2354                                    end if;
2355                    
2356                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2357                                -- Suspend transmission
2358                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2359                                when s_pc_suspend =>
2360       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_ena <= '1';
2361       1/1                          perform_hsync <= '1';
2362       1/1                          crc_spec_enable_i <= '1';
2363       1/1                          bit_err_disable <= '1';
2364       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_suspend <= '1';
2365                    
2366       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
2367       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
2368       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
2369       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_BASE_ID_DURATION;
2370       1/1                              tx_load_base_id_i <= '1';
2371       1/1                              sof_pulse_i <= '1';
2372       1/1                              set_receiver_i <= '1';
2373       1/1                              destuff_enable_set <= '1';
2374       1/1                              rx_clear_i <= '1';
2375                    
2376                                    -- End of Suspend -> Unit goes to IDLE if there is nothing to transmitt, otherwise
2377                                    -- it goes to SOF and transmitts
2378                                    elsif (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
2379       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
2380       1/1                              if (tx_frame_ready = '1') then
2381       1/1                                  set_transmitter_i <= '1';
2382       1/1                                  txtb_hw_cmd_d.lock <= '1';
2383       1/1                                  rx_clear_i <= '1';
2384       1/1                                  destuff_enable_set <= '1';
2385       1/1                                  stuff_enable_set <= '1';
2386                                        else
2387       1/1                                  set_idle_i <= '1';
2388                                        end if;
2389                                    end if;
2390                    
2391                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2392                                -- Unit is in Bus idle period.
2393                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2394                                when s_pc_idle =>
2395       1/1                          perform_hsync <= '1';
2396       1/1                          crc_spec_enable_i <= '1';
2397       1/1                          bit_err_disable <= '1';
2398                    
2399       1/1                          if (is_bus_off = '0') then
2400       1/1                              if (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
2401       1/1                                  tick_state_reg <= '1';
2402       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
2403       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_BASE_ID_DURATION;
2404       1/1                                  sof_pulse_i <= '1';
2405       1/1                                  crc_enable <= '1';
2406                                        end if;
2407                    
2408       1/1                              if (tx_frame_ready = '1') then
2409       1/1                                  tick_state_reg <= '1';
2410       1/1                                  txtb_hw_cmd_d.lock <= '1';
2411       1/1                                  set_transmitter_i <= '1';
2412       1/1                                  tx_load_base_id_i <= '1';
2413       1/1                                  stuff_enable_set <= '1';
2414                    
2415       1/1                                  if (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
2416       1/1                                      tx_frame_no_sof_d <= '1';
2417                                            end if;
2418                    
2419                                        elsif (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
2420       1/1                                  set_receiver_i <= '1';
2421                                        end if;
2422                    
2423                                        -- Transmission/reception started -> Enable Bit de-stuffing! Clear RX Shift
2424                                        -- register!
2425       1/1                              if (frame_start = '1') then
2426       1/1                                  destuff_enable_set <= '1';
2427       1/1                                  rx_clear_i <= '1';
2428                                        end if;
2429                    
2430                                    -- If we are bus-off we need to move to wait for reintegration command!
2431                                    else
2432       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
2433                                    end if;
2434                    
2435                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2436                                -- Wait till command from User to start re-integration!
2437                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2438                                when s_pc_reintegrating_wait =>
2439       1/1                          bit_err_disable <= '1';
2440                    
2441       1/1                          if (mr_command_ercrst_q = '1') then
2442       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
2443       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
2444       1/1                              reinteg_ctr_clr <= '1';
2445       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_INTEGRATION_DURATION;
2446       1/1                              clr_bus_off_rst_flg <= '1';
2447                                    end if;
2448                    
2449                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2450                                -- Unit is re-integrating, waiting till re-integration counter expires!
2451                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2452                                when s_pc_reintegrating =>
2453       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_ena <= '1';
2454       1/1                          perform_hsync <= '1';
2455       1/1                          bit_err_disable <= '1';
2456                    
2457                                    -- Restart integration upon reception of DOMINANT bit or upon synchronization edge.
2458       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT or sync_edge = '1') then
2459       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_INTEGRATION_DURATION;
2460                                    end if;
2461                    
2462                                    -- When preloaded due to synchronisation edge, this is outside of sample point!
2463       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
2464       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
2465                                    end if;
2466                    
2467       1/1                          if (sync_edge = '1' and
2468                                       -- Third reset condition shall be valid for nodes which are CAN FD tolerant or
2469                                       -- CAN FD enabled!
2470                                       (not(mr_settings_pex = '0' and mr_mode_fde = '0')))
2471                                    then
2472       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_unaliged <= '1';
2473                                    end if;
2474                    
2475       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
2476       1/1                              reinteg_ctr_enable <= '1';
2477                                    end if;
2478                    
2479       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1' and reinteg_ctr_expired = '0') then
2480       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
2481       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_INTEGRATION_DURATION;
2482                                    end if;
2483                    
2484       1/1                          if (reinteg_ctr_expired = '1' and ctrl_ctr_zero = '1' and rx_trigger = '1') then
2485       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
2486       1/1                              set_idle_i <= '1';
2487       1/1                              set_err_active_i <= '1';
2488       1/1                              load_init_vect_i <= '1';
2489                                    end if;
2490                    
2491                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2492                                -- Active error flag.
2493                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2494                                when s_pc_act_err_flag =>
2495       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_ena <= '1';
2496       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_err <= '1';
2497       1/1                          tx_dominant <= '1';
2498       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_ERR;
2499                    
2500       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
2501       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
2502       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
2503       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_DELIM_WAIT_DURATION;
2504       1/1                              first_err_delim_d <= '1';
2505                                    end if;
2506                    
2507                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2508                                -- Passive error flag.
2509                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2510                                when s_pc_pas_err_flag =>
2511       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_ena <= '1';
2512       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_err <= '1';
2513       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_ERR;
2514                    
2515                                    -- Node sending Passive error flag may receive RECESSIVE or DOMINANT, and DOMINANT
2516                                    -- shall not be treated as bit error!
2517       1/1                          bit_err_disable <= '1';
2518                    
2519                                    -- Reseting control counter if different bit that previous is detected. Passive
2520                                    -- error flag must be completed after 6 bits of equal polarity!
2521       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs_prev /= rx_data_nbs) then
2522       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i   <= '1';
2523       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_SHORTENED_ERR_FLG_DURATION;
2524                                    elsif (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
2525       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
2526       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
2527       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_DELIM_WAIT_DURATION;
2528       1/1                              first_err_delim_d <= '1';
2529                                    end if;
2530                    
2531                                    -- If dominant bit is detected, and previous error was ACK, then TEC shall be
2532                                    -- still incremented!
2533       1/1                          if (ack_err_flag = '1' and rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT and rx_trigger = '1') then
2534       1/1                              bit_err_after_ack_err <= '1';
2535       1/1                              ack_err_flag_clr <= '1';
2536                                    end if;
2537                    
2538                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2539                                -- Wait till Error delimiter (detection of recessive bit)
2540                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2541                                when s_pc_err_delim_wait =>
2542       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_err <= '1';
2543       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_ERR;
2544       1/1                          ack_err_flag_clr <= '1';
2545                    
2546                                    -- When waiting for RECESSIVE bit after Error flag, unit may receive DOMINANT and
2547                                    -- not interpret this as Bit error!
2548       1/1                          bit_err_disable <= '1';
2549                    
2550       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '0') then
2551       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_ena <= '1';
2552                                    else
2553       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
2554                                    end if;
2555                    
2556       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE) then
2557       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
2558       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
2559       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_ERR_DELIM_DURATION;
2560                                    end if;
2561                    
2562                                    -- Node received dominant bit as first bit after Error flag! This shall be treated
2563                                    -- as primary error
2564       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT and first_err_delim_q = '1') then
2565       1/1                              primary_err_i <= '1';
2566       1/1                              first_err_delim_d <= '0';
2567                                    end if;
2568                    
2569                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2570                                -- 13 dominant bits (6 error flag + 7 error delimiter) has been detected (active error
2571                                -- flag), or 7 has been detected (passive error flag).
2572                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2573                                when s_pc_err_flag_too_long =>
2574       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_err <= '1';
2575       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_ERR;
2576       1/1                          bit_err_disable <= '1';
2577       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_ena <= '1';
2578                    
2579       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE) then
2580       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
2581       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
2582       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_ERR_DELIM_DURATION;
2583                    
2584                                    -- This indicates that either 14th dominant bit was detected, or each next
2585                                    -- consecutive 8 DOMINANT bits were detected!
2586                                    elsif (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
2587       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
2588       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
2589       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_DOMINANT_REPEAT_DURATION;
2590       1/1                              err_delim_late_i <= '1';
2591                                    end if;
2592                    
2593                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2594                                -- 13 dominant bits (6 overload flag + 7 overload delimiter) has been detected.
2595                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2596                                when s_pc_ovr_flag_too_long =>
2597       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_overload <= '1';
2598       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_OVRL;
2599       1/1                          bit_err_disable <= '1';
2600       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_ena <= '1';
2601                    
2602       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE) then
2603       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
2604       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
2605       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_OVR_DELIM_DURATION;
2606                    
2607                                    -- This indicates that either 14th dominant bit was detected, or each next
2608                                    -- consecutive 8 DOMINANT bits were detected!
2609                                    elsif (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
2610       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
2611       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
2612       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_DOMINANT_REPEAT_DURATION;
2613       1/1                              err_delim_late_i <= '1';
2614                                    end if;
2615                    
2616                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2617                                -- Error delimiter
2618                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2619                                when s_pc_err_delim =>
2620       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_err <= '1';
2621       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_ena <= '1';
2622       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_ERR;
2623       1/1                          bit_err_disable <= '1';
2624                    
2625       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
2626       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
2627       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
2628                    
2629       1/1                              if (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
2630       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_OVR_FLG_DURATION;
2631                                        else
2632       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_INTERMISSION_DURATION;
2633                                        end if;
2634                                    elsif (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
2635       1/1                              form_err_i <= '1';
2636                                    end if;
2637                    
2638                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2639                                -- Overload flag
2640                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2641                                when s_pc_ovr_flag =>
2642       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_overload <= '1';
2643       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_ena <= '1';
2644       1/1                          tx_dominant <= '1';
2645       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_OVRL;
2646                    
2647       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
2648       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
2649       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
2650       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_DELIM_WAIT_DURATION;
2651                                    end if;
2652                    
2653                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2654                                -- Wait till overload delimiter.
2655                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2656                                when s_pc_ovr_delim_wait =>
2657       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_overload <= '1';
2658       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_OVRL;
2659                    
2660       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '0') then
2661       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_ena <= '1';
2662                                    else
2663       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
2664                                    end if;
2665                    
2666                                    -- When waiting for RECESSIVE bit after Overload flag, unit may receive DOMINANT
2667                                    -- and not interpret this as Bit error!
2668       1/1                          bit_err_disable <= '1';
2669                    
2670       1/1                          if (rx_data_nbs = RECESSIVE) then
2671       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
2672       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
2673       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_OVR_DELIM_DURATION;
2674                                    end if;
2675                    
2676                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2677                                -- Overload delimiter
2678                                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2679                                when s_pc_ovr_delim  =>
2680       1/1                          ctrl_ctr_ena <= '1';
2681       1/1                          pc_dbg.is_overload <= '1';
2682       1/1                          err_pos <= ERC_POS_OVRL;
2683       1/1                          bit_err_disable <= '1';
2684                    
2685       1/1                          if (ctrl_ctr_zero = '1') then
2686       1/1                              tick_state_reg <= '1';
2687       1/1                              ctrl_ctr_pload_i <= '1';
2688                    
2689       1/1                              if (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
2690       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_OVR_FLG_DURATION;
2691                                        else
2692       1/1                                  ctrl_ctr_pload_val <= C_INTERMISSION_DURATION;
2693                                        end if;
2694                                    elsif (rx_data_nbs = DOMINANT) then
2695       1/1                              form_err_i <= '1';
2696                                    end if;
2697                    
2698                                end case;
2699                            end if;
2700                    
2701                        end process;
2702                    
2703                        -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2704                        -- FSM State register
2705                        -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2706                        state_reg_ce <= '1' when (tick_state_reg = '1' and ctrl_signal_upd = '1')
2707                                            else
2708                                        '0';
2709                    
2710                        fsm_state_reg_proc : process(clk_sys, res_n)
2711                        begin
2712       1/1                  if (res_n = '0') then
2713       1/1                      curr_state <= s_pc_off;
2714                            elsif (rising_edge(clk_sys)) then
2715       1/1                      if (state_reg_ce = '1') then
2716       1/1                          curr_state <= next_state;
2717                                end if;
2718                            end if;
2719                        end process;
2720                    
2721                        -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2722                        -- Control counter is preloaded:
2723                        --  1. When core is off and becomes non-off
2724                        --  2. When preloaded by any state and RX trigger is active. This saves gating with RX Trigger
2725                        --     in each FSM state!
2726                        --  3. When counter is reset during integration due to synchronisation edge. This can be
2727                        --     anytime, not just in sample point!
2728                        -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2729                        ctrl_ctr_pload <= ctrl_ctr_pload_i when (curr_state = s_pc_off) else
2730                                          ctrl_ctr_pload_i when (ctrl_signal_upd = '1') else
2731                                          '1' when (ctrl_ctr_pload_unaliged = '1') else
2732                                          '0';
2733                    
2734                        -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2735                        -- Registering control commands to RX Buffer due to following reasons
2736                        --  1. In last bit of DLC, DLC is not yet sampled in RX Shift register, thus we need to delay
2737                        --     storing of metadata word by one clock cycle!
2738                        --  2. Break possible long combinational paths between RX Buffer and Protocol control FSM!
2739                        -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2740                        rx_buf_cmds_proc : process(clk_sys, res_n)
2741                        begin
2742       1/1                  if (res_n = '0') then
2743       1/1                      store_metadata     <= '0';
2744       1/1                      store_data         <= '0';
2745       1/1                      rec_valid          <= '0';
2746       1/1                      rec_abort          <= '0';
2747                            elsif (rising_edge(clk_sys)) then
2748                    
2749                                -- Frame is stored to RX Buffer when unit is either receiver or loopback mode is
2750                                -- enabled. Each command is active only for one clock cycle!
2751       1/1                      if ((is_receiver = '1' or mr_settings_ilbp = '1') and
2752                                    ((rx_trigger = '1') or (err_frm_req = '1')))
2753                                then
2754       1/1                          store_metadata     <= store_metadata_d;
2755       1/1                          store_data         <= store_data_d;
2756       1/1                          rec_valid          <= rec_valid_d;
2757       1/1                          rec_abort          <= rec_abort_d;
2758                                else
2759       1/1                          store_metadata     <= '0';
2760       1/1                          store_data         <= '0';
2761       1/1                          rec_valid          <= '0';
2762       1/1                          rec_abort          <= '0';
2763                                end if;
2764                            end if;
2765                        end process;
2766                    
2767                        ctrl_signal_upd <= '1' when (rx_trigger = '1' or err_frm_req = '1')
2768                                               else
2769                                           '0';
2770                    
2771                        -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2772                        -- TXT Buffer HW commands pipeline
2773                        -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2774                        txtb_hw_cmd_proc : process(clk_sys, res_n)
2775                        begin
2776       1/1                  if (res_n = '0') then
2777       1/1                      txtb_hw_cmd_q.lock    <= '0';
2778       1/1                      txtb_hw_cmd_q.unlock  <= '0';
2779       1/1                      txtb_hw_cmd_q.valid   <= '0';
2780       1/1                      txtb_hw_cmd_q.err     <= '0';
2781       1/1                      txtb_hw_cmd_q.arbl    <= '0';
2782       1/1                      txtb_hw_cmd_q.failed  <= '0';
2783                            elsif (rising_edge(clk_sys)) then
2784       1/1                      if (ctrl_signal_upd = '1') then
2785       1/1                          txtb_hw_cmd_q <= txtb_hw_cmd_d;
2786                                else
2787       1/1                          txtb_hw_cmd_q <= ('0', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0');
2788                                end if;
2789                            end if;
2790                        end process;
2791                    
2792                        -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2793                        -- RX Shift register commands gating. Each command can be active only in sample point
2794                        -- (rx_trigger = '1')!
2795                        -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2796                        rx_store_base_id <= rx_store_base_id_i and rx_trigger;
2797                        rx_store_ext_id <= rx_store_ext_id_i and rx_trigger;
2798                        rx_store_ide <= rx_store_ide_i and rx_trigger;
2799                        rx_store_rtr <= rx_store_rtr_i and rx_trigger;
2800                        rx_store_edl <= rx_store_edl_i and rx_trigger;
2801                        rx_store_dlc <= rx_store_dlc_i and rx_trigger;
2802                        rx_store_esi <= rx_store_esi_i and rx_trigger;
2803                        rx_store_brs <= rx_store_brs_i and rx_trigger;
2804                        rx_store_stuff_count <= rx_store_stuff_count_i and rx_trigger;
2805                    
2806                        -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2807                        -- TX Shift register commands gating. Each command can be active only in sample point
2808                        -- (rx_trigger = '1')!
2809                        -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2810                        tx_load_base_id <= tx_load_base_id_i and rx_trigger;
2811                        tx_load_ext_id <= tx_load_ext_id_i and rx_trigger;
2812                        tx_load_dlc <= tx_load_dlc_i and rx_trigger;
2813                        tx_load_data_word <= tx_load_data_word_i and rx_trigger;
2814                        tx_load_stuff_count <= tx_load_stuff_count_i and rx_trigger;
2815                        tx_load_crc <= tx_load_crc_i and rx_trigger;
2816                    
2817                        -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2818                        -- TX Shift register is enabled only when the unit is transmitter!
2819                        -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2820                        tx_shift_ena <= '1' when (tx_shift_ena_i = '1' and is_transmitter = '1')
2821                                            else
2822                                        '0';
2823                    
2824                        -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2825                        -- Error signalling gating. Each command can be active only in sample point (rx_trigger = '1')!
2826                        -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2827                        form_err <= form_err_i and rx_trigger;
2828                        ack_err <= ack_err_i and rx_trigger;
2829                        crc_err <= crc_err_i and rx_trigger;
2830                        bit_err_arb <= bit_err_arb_i and rx_trigger;
2831                        decrement_rec <= decrement_rec_i and rx_trigger;
2832                    
2833                        -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2834                        -- Switching of Bit-rate
2835                        -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2836                        switch_to_ssp <= '1' when (sp_control_switch_data = '1' and is_transmitter = '1' and
2837                                                   mr_ssp_cfg_ssp_src /= SSP_SRC_NO_SSP)
2838                                             else
2839                                         '0';
2840                    
2841                        sp_control_d <=   NOMINAL_SAMPLE when (sp_control_switch_nominal = '1')
2842                                                         else
2843                                        SECONDARY_SAMPLE when (switch_to_ssp = '1')
2844                                                         else
2845                                             DATA_SAMPLE when (sp_control_switch_data = '1')
2846                                                         else
2847                                            sp_control_q_i;
2848                    
2849                        sp_control_ce <= '1' when (sp_control_switch_nominal = '1') else
2850                                         '1' when (sp_control_switch_data = '1') else
2851                                         '0';
2852                    
2853                        sp_control_reg_proc : process(clk_sys, res_n)
2854                        begin
2855       1/1                  if (res_n = '0') then
2856       1/1                      sp_control_q_i <= NOMINAL_SAMPLE;
2857                            elsif (rising_edge(clk_sys)) then
2858       1/1                      if (sp_control_ce = '1') then
2859       1/1                          sp_control_q_i <= sp_control_d;
2860                                end if;
2861                            end if;
2862                        end process;
2863                    
2864                        sp_control <= sp_control_d when (br_shifted_i = '1') else
2865                                      sp_control_q_i;
2866                    
2867                        -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2868                        -- Indicates that Active Error or Overload flag is being transmitted! Can't be part of current
2869                        -- state, since it must be valid also during error condition to distiguish error during error
2870                        -- flag!
2871                        -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2872                        act_err_ovr_flag <= '1' when (curr_state = s_pc_act_err_flag) else
2873                                            '1' when (curr_state = s_pc_ovr_flag) else
2874                                            '0';
2875                    
2876                        first_err_delim_flag_reg : process(clk_sys, res_n)
2877                        begin
2878       1/1                  if (res_n = '0') then
2879       1/1                      first_err_delim_q <= '0';
2880                            elsif (rising_edge(clk_sys)) then
2881       1/1                      if (rx_trigger = '1') then
2882       1/1                          first_err_delim_q <= first_err_delim_d;
2883                                end if;
2884                            end if;
2885                        end process;
2886                    
2887                        -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2888                        -- Detection of primary error and late error delimiter must be active only for one clock cycle
2889                        -- in Sample point (rx_trigger)!
2890                        -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
